result.execSummary:
Kyle M. Woodman was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Kyle M. Woodman was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Case called at 9:32 AM 
Prosecuting Attorney Matthew Z Kirkpatrick in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Kyle M. Woodman in court, in custody with Attorney Ryan Moertel.
Defendant waives his right to Extradition Hearing and signs the waiver in court. Court in forms the Defendant of his Extradition rights and signs Waiver of Extradition.

(Case called at 11:31 AM- by Zoom) Defendant Kyle Woodman appears in custody via video conference from the Jail with Attorney Zebulon Patek. ADA Trenton Piltz appears in person for the State of Wisconsin. 
Extradition- Defense waives reading of the complaint. Defense indicates the Defendant is not willing to sign the waiver of extradition until he can speak to his attorneys. State requests $20,000 cash bond. Court orders $20,000 cash bond. 
Extradition Hearing: 06/13/2022 at 9:30 AM.
